      "title": "太...了 (tài...le) — Too / Excessively",
      "explanation": "太(tài) + Adjective + 了(le) expresses excess. 太(tài) alone without 了(le) can mean 'very' in casual speech, but 太(tài)...了(le) emphasizes too much. Formula: Subject + 太(tài) + Adjective + 了(le).",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "今天太热了！",
          "pinyin": "Jīntiān tài rè le!",
          "english": "It's too hot today!"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "这个太大了。",
          "pinyin": "Zhège tài dà le.",
          "english": "This is too big."
        }
      ],
